1-**Task Objective**
    a-Analyze housing data
    b-Identify important features affecting house prices
    c-Train a machine learning model to predict prices
    d-Evaluate the performance of the model

2-**Dataset Used**
    a-Area / Size of the house
    b-Number of bedrooms
    c-Number of bathrooms
    d-Location
    e-Price (main target)

3-**Clear Problem Statement and Goal**
  Problem Statement:
      Given various features of a house, predict its market price.
  Goal:
      Develop a model that can:
        Learn relationships between features and price
        Predict prices with minimum error

4-**Data Loading**
      The dataset was loaded using standard data handling libraries like pandas.

5-**Data Preprocessing Steps**
    a-Checked for missing values
    b-Cleaned inconsistent data (if any)
    c-Selected relevant features
    d-Split data into:
    ---->Training set
    ---->Testing set

6-**Models Applied**
  Linear Regression
    a-A basic yet powerful algorithm for regression problems
    b-Assumes a linear relationship between input features and output

7-**Key Results and Findings**
    a-Area (size) is the most influential factor in determining house price
    b-Number of rooms also impacts price significantly
    c-Linear Regression provides reasonable accuracy
    d-Model performance depends heavily on feature quality











